<subSubSection id="C315654D7BF1038FEEF8FEE0FE2EFE08" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB036C67BF1038FEEF8FEE0FD33FE2D" blockId="137.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FEEF8FEE0FE89FE98" bold="true" box="[199,335,332,357]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FEF69FEE0FD95FE99" box="[342,595,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Paralecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vacerra">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FEF69FEE0FD95FE99" box="[342,595,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Paralecanium vacerra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FED58FEE0FBC3FE98" box="[871,1029,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Paralecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FED58FEE0FBC3FE98" box="[871,1029,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Paralecanium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with only a single stigmatic spine in each stigmatic cleft; but the stigmatic spines on 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FED24FEDDFC49FE75" box="[795,911,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Paralecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vacerra">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FED24FEDDFC49FE75" box="[795,911,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">P. vacerra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are short and very stout. It also has dissimilar claw digitules on the prothoracic legs, whereas they are similar (both broad) on the meso- and metathoracic legs. Claw digitules are similar on all legs on other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB036C67BF1038FEEF8FE70FE2EFE08" blockId="137.[151,1437,151,573]" box="[199,488,476,501]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FEEF8FE70FE88FE08" bold="true" box="[199,334,476,501]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Host-plant.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FEF6BFE70FE22FE08" box="[340,484,476,501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Orchidaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C315654D7BF1038FEEF8FE53FC5CFDC0" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB036C67BF1038FEEF8FE53FC5CFDC0" blockId="137.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FEEF8FE53FE51FDE5" bold="true" box="[199,407,511,536]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Name derivation.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FEC48FDADFD08FDE5" box="[631,718,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Paralecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vacerra">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FEC48FDADFD08FDE5" box="[631,718,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">vacerra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is taken from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D457BF1038FED4AFDADFBDCFDE5" authority=", Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[885,1050,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Paralecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vacerra">
<emphasis id="B97BEAD47BF1038FED4AFDADFC0AFDE5" box="[885,972,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">vacerra</emphasis>
, Latin
</taxonomicName>
, f, for log or post, referring to the single stout stigmatic spine in each cleft, and is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
